{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.31",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 31,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 31 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:1",
      "text": "The words of king Lamuel. The vision wherewith his mother instructed him.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:2",
      "text": "What, O my beloved, what, O the beloved of my womb, what, O the beloved of my vows?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:3",
      "text": "Give not thy substance to women, and thy riches to destroy kings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:4",
      "text": "Give not to kings, O Lamuel, give not wine to kings: because there is no secret where drunkenness reigneth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:5",
      "text": "And lest they drink and forget judgments, and pervert the cause of the children of the poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:6",
      "text": "Give strong drink to them that are sad; and wine to them that are grieved in mind:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:7",
      "text": "Let them drink, and forget their want, and remember their sorrow no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:8",
      "text": "Open thy mouth for the dumb, and for the causes of all the children that pass.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:9",
      "text": "Open thy mouth, decree that which is just, and do justice to the needy and poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:10",
      "text": "Who shall find a valiant woman? far, and from the uttermost coasts is the price of her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:11",
      "text": "The heart of her husband trusteth in her, and he shall have no need of spoils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:12",
      "text": "She will render him good, and not evil all the days of her life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:13",
      "text": "She hath sought wool and flax, and hath wrought by the counsel of her hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:14",
      "text": "She is like the merchant's ship, she bringeth her bread from afar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:15",
      "text": "And she hath risen in the night, and given a prey to her household, and victuals to her maidens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:16",
      "text": "She hath considered a field, and bought it: with the fruit of her hands she hath planted a vineyard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:17",
      "text": "She hath girded her loins with strength, and hath strengthened her arm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:18",
      "text": "She hath tasted, and seen that her traffic is good: her lamp shall not be put out in the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:19",
      "text": "She hath put out her hand to strong things, and her fingers have taken hold of the spindle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:20",
      "text": "She hath opened her hand to the needy, and stretched out her hands to the poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:21",
      "text": "She shall not fear for her house in the cold of snow: for all her domestics are clothed with double garments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:22",
      "text": "She hath made for herself clothing of tapestry: fine linen, and purple, is her covering.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:23",
      "text": "Her husband is honourable in the gates, when he sitteth among the senators of the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:24",
      "text": "She made fine linen, and sold it, and delivered a girdle to the Chanaanite.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:25",
      "text": "Strength and beauty are her clothing, and she shall laugh in the latter day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:26",
      "text": "She hath opened her mouth to wisdom, and the law of clemency is on her tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:27",
      "text": "She hath looked well on the paths of her house, and hath not eaten her bread idle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:28",
      "text": "Her children rose up, and called her blessed: her husband, and he praised her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:29",
      "text": "Many daughters have gathered together riches: thou hast surpassed them all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:30",
      "text": "Favour is deceitful, and beauty is vain: the woman that feareth the Lord, she shall be praised.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.31.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 31:31",
      "text": "Give her of the fruit of her hands: and let her works praise her in the gates.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
